Just removes:
- `use std::ffi::OsString;`
- `fn subcommand()` 
- `fn args()`

The 6 custom commands (build, run, test, compare, install, version) only lose the dead code. The 3 simple passthroughs (clean, clippy, fmt) gain a few lines by inlining args building into `execute()`.
